3Cli%3EShe%20had%20no%20access%20to%20money%20or%20signal%20during%20the%2014-hour%20blackout%20which%20brought%20life%20to%20a%20standstill.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20experience%20made%20Duncan%20rethink%20what%20cash%20she%20carries%2C%20what%20she%20stocks%20and%20even%20her%20income.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20at%20midday%2C%20I%20was%20on%20the%20phone%20with%20my%20boyfriend%20when%20it%20unexpectedly%20cut%20off.%20I%20continued%20walking%20down%20the%20street%20in%20Granada%2C%20where%20I%20live%2C%20not%20thinking%20much%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOblivious%20to%20the%20non-functioning%20traffic%20lights%2C%20I%20arrived%20at%20my%20local%20deli.%20The%20shop%20lights%20were%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BApag%C3%B3n%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20frustrated%20woman%20behind%20the%20counter%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPower%20cut.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGranadians%20are%20famous%20for%20being%20a%20little%20grumpy%2C%20but%20this%20was%20different%3B%20she%20looked%20alarmed.%20In%20a%20flurry%20of%20Andalucian%20words%2C%20I%20picked%20out%20%26quot%3BNo%20hay%20luz%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20translates%20to%20%26quot%3Bno%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bfatal%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20self-explanatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b86444f4-131d-49ae-82d3-49d8854c6b8b%5C%22%3EA%20blackout%20had%20hit%20multiple%20European%20countries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20would%20be%20many%20more%20hours%20before%20I%20would%20find%20out%2C%20a%20power%20cut%20had%20struck%20all%20of%20Spain%20and%20Portugal%2C%20and%20hospitals%20switched%20to%20emergency%20generators.%20Pedro%20S%3Cspan%3E%C3%A1%3C%2Fspan%3Enchez%20was%20declaring%20it%20a%20national%20emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20hot%20deli%2C%20delicious%20cheeses%2C%20homemade%20stews%2C%20and%20expensive%20meats%2C%20usually%20refrigerated%2C%20were%20sweating%20and%20sagging.%20The%20card%20machine%20wasn't%20functioning.%20I%20found%20a%20two-euro%20coin%20in%20my%20pocket%20and%20bought%20the%20last%20baguette.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalking%20out%20onto%20the%20street%2C%20there%20was%20an%20unsettling%20buzz.%20Granada%20is%20usually%20peaceful%20and%20sleepy%2C%20but%20people%20seemed%20on%20edge.%20Heading%20into%20the%20local%20fruit%20store%2C%20I%20found%20the%20same%20scene%3A%20no%20card%20payments%2C%20lights%2C%20or%20fridge%2C%20tense%20shopkeepers%2C%20and%20alarmed%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20my%20change%20from%20the%20bread%20to%20pay%20cash%20for%20an%20avocado%20and%20hurried%20home.%20I%20Googled%20what%20had%20happened%2C%20but%20a%20blank%20screen%20stared%20back%20at%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20calling%20my%20boyfriend%2C%20but%20I%20couldn't%20get%20through.%20I%20knew%20he%20was%20at%20his%20office%20and%20wondered%20if%20he%20could%20be%20trapped%20inside%20the%20electric%20doors.%20A%20latent%20SMS%20had%20arrived%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20ok%3F%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20couldn't%20reply.%20No%20matter%20how%20often%20I%20switched%20my%20SIM%20card%2C%20I%20couldn't%20get%20more%20than%20a%20second%20of%20glitchy%20signal.%20Another%20one%20came%20through%3A%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20scary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22474abf86-d0ae-4158-b1a8-69a2f9bca4ff%5C%22%3EPeople%20thought%20it%20could%20be%20the%20start%20of%20WWIII%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20sat%20in%20my%20small%20loft%20apartment%2C%20smearing%20avocado%20on%20untoasted%20bread.%20Questions%20sprinted%20through%20my%20mind.%20Should%20I%20go%20looking%20for%20my%20boyfriend%3F%20How%20can%20I%20contact%20my%20clients%20about%20deadlines%20due%20today%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20importantly%2C%20how%20much%20of%20this%20bread%20and%20avocado%20do%20I%20need%20to%20save%20for%20us%20for%20dinner%2C%20because%20there%20was%20nothing%20else%2C%20and%20I%20only%20had%2044%20cents%20left%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20working%20in%20London%20when%20I%20met%20my%20Andalucian%20boyfriend%20around%20six%20years%20ago.%20I%20started%20working%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer%20and%2C%20with%20time%2C%20we%20came%20to%20realise%20we'd%20have%20a%20better%20life%20in%20Spain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20lived%20in%20Granada%20for%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%2C%20and%20my%20freelance%20work%20hasn't%20been%20affected%20until%20Monday.%2014%20hours%20of%20zero%20electricity%20unravelled%20my%20income%20faster%20than%20a%20pandemic%2C%20Brexit%2C%20or%20loss%20of%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20heard%20my%20boyfriend's%20keys%2C%20I%20felt%20relieved.%20He%20told%20me%20the%20only%20news%20was%20coming%20from%20car%20radios.%20Pedro%20S%3Cspan%3E%C3%A1%3C%2Fspan%3Enchez%20was%20instructing%20people%20to%20use%20the%20emergency%20services%20sparingly.%20There%20were%20blocks%20and%20back-ups%20in%20petrol%20stations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETogether%2C%20we%20walked%20into%20the%20city.%20Most%20shops%20were%20shut%2C%20their%20staff%20sat%20outside%20on%20park%20benches%20%E2%80%94%20if%20not%2C%20they%20were%20taking%20cash%20payments%20and%20writing%20receipts%20by%20hand.%20A%20man%20was%20running%20between%20shops%2C%20frantic%20and%20aghast.%20As%20the%20proprietor%20of%20a%20chain%20of%20ice%20cream%20stores%2C%20he%20watched%20his%20profits%20melt%20down%20the%20sides%20of%20non-functioning%20freezers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20local%20big%20supermarket%20was%20accepting%20card%20payments%20using%20an%20emergency%20generator.%20Shoppers%20loaded%20their%20carts%20in%20a%20quiet%20frenzy.%20In%20the%20blue%20light%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20something%20out%20of%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Mirror.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fridges%20and%20freezers%20were%20all%20closed.%20Everyone%20was%20hunting%20down%20food%20that%20didn't%20need%20cooking%20or%20storing%20in%20a%20cold%20place.%20Items%20like%20bread%20and%20candles%20were%20long%20gone%2C%20and%20the%20canned%20goods%20shelves%20were%20bare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20were%20also%20loading%20up%20on%20water%20and%20toilet%20paper%20as%20rumors%20spread%20that%20the%20power%20cut%20was%20a%20Russian%20attack%20and%20World%20War%20III%20was%20here.%20Carrying%20our%20bags%20home%2C%20my%20boyfriend%20translated%20conversations%20he%20overheard.%20A%20competing%20theory%20was%20that%20the%20climate%20crisis%20was%20finally%20striking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229e5f1103-aeda-4ae0-ba73-e672071c8577%5C%22%3ECommunities%20rallied%20in%20the%20dark%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20immigrant%20with%20just%2044%20cents%20in%20my%20pocket%20and%20no%20way%20to%20earn%20an%20income%2C%20I%20felt%20increasingly%20vulnerable.%20But%20my%20boyfriend%20reassured%20me%2C%20%26quot%3BAndalucians%20share.%20Communities%20look%20out%20for%20each%20other.%20We'll%20be%20okay.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20right.%20The%20panic%20in%20the%20streets%20was%20also%20intertwined%20with%20neighbours%20singing%20and%20clapping.%20Walking%20back%20to%20our%20loft%2C%20locals%20met%20in%20the%20squares%20around%20our%20block.%20My%20part%20of%20Granada%20is%20famously%20alternative.%20A%20few%20people%20blasted%20car%20radios%20or%20brought%20out%20guitars.%20Flamenco%20jams%20carried%20long%20into%20the%20night%2C%20illuminated%20by%20car%20lights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20fell%20asleep%20admiring%20the%20stars%20through%20the%20open%20window%2C%20more%20visible%20than%20I'd%20ever%20seen%20them%20in%20Spain.%20When%20the%20power%20returned%20at%202%20a.m.%2C%20I%20was%20woken%20up%20by%20the%20crowd's%20roar%2C%20swiftly%20followed%20by%20my%20boyfriend%20flipping%20the%20light%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20schools%20reopened%20and%20traffic%20flowed%2C%20almost%20like%20nothing%20had%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20looked%20tired%2C%20and%20many%20businesses%20stayed%20closed%20as%20they%20took%20stock%20of%20their%20losses.%20Picking%20up%20my%20daily%20coffee%2C%20the%20barista%20looked%20distracted.%20She%20told%20me%20that%20she'd%20been%20able%20to%20save%20most%20of%20her%20baked%20goods%20from%20the%20heat%2C%20but%20couldn't%20sell%20hot%20drinks%20yesterday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cba55b3-9ffc-4720-92c3-ecb99b413a9e%5C%22%3EI%20learned%20some%20powerful%20lessons%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'll%20work%20this%20weekend%20to%20make%20up%20some%20of%20the%20time%20I%20lost%20on%20Monday%2C%20but%20I%20am%20also%20making%20changes.%20A%2020%20euro%20note%20is%20in%20my%20purse%2C%20where%20it%20will%20remain%20as%20a%20new%20emergency%20fund.%20Tins%20of%20sweetcorn%2C%20chickpeas%2C%20and%20hummus%20are%20also%20in%20the%20cupboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20also%20going%20to%20reevaluate%20my%20income.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20it's%20too%20dependent%20on%20the%20internet.%20I'm%20considering%20offering%20English%20lessons%20or%20transforming%20the%20guest%20room%20into%20a%20makeshift%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20is%20for%20sure%3A%20I%20am%20not%20leaving%20Andalusia.%20Even%20at%20its%20worst%20moments%2C%20this%20place%20offers%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20warmth%20that%20no%20power%20cut%20could%20ever%20put%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspain-blackout-felt-like-black-mirror-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746264181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6814e5d23fe8d3928364c28f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspain-blackout-felt-like-black-mirror-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Spain%20and%20Portugal%20experienced%20nationwide%20blackouts%20on%20Monday.%20Writer%20Hannah%20Duncan%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Granada%2C%20said%20it%20taught%20her%20an%20important%20lesson.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Duncan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspain-blackout-felt-like-black-mirror-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ca