lture%20isn't%20a%20given%20and%20identified%202%20issues%20that%20needed%20to%20be%20tackled.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJassy%20said%20remote%20work%20stifles%20innovation%20and%20gets%20in%20the%20way%20of%20culture%20being%20taught.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EManagement%20layers%20are%20another%20key%20area%20that%20Amazon%20is%20seeking%20to%20reduce.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Jassy%20said%20he%20thinks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-amazon-history-facts-2017-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20a%20strong%20company%20culture%2C%20but%20staying%20that%20way%20isn't%20a%20given%20as%20the%20company%20expands%20and%20parts%20of%20the%20business%20evolve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20keep%20working%20on%20strengthening%20the%20parts%20of%20your%20culture%20that%20you%20see%20being%20stretched%20if%20you%20want%20to%20keep%20being%20successful%20culturally%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20during%20a%20speaking%20event%20at%20the%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%20Leadership%20Summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20effort%20to%20restore%20Amazon's%20strong%20sense%20of%20culture%2C%20the%20company%20rolled%20out%20several%20changes%2C%20including%20a%205-day%20return%20to%20office.%20The%20CEO%20said%20the%20company%20pinpointed%20two%20problem%20areas%20it%20needed%20to%20tackle%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandy-jassy-advice-cut-bureaucracy-management-layers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%20work%20and%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa7cc450-8068-4c5e-b474-5a32904a7da5%5C%22%3ECulture%20can't%20be%20taught%20remotely%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20many%20of%20the%20company's%20inventions%20have%20emerged%20from%20%26quot%3Bmessy%2C%20wandering%20meetings%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20things%20may%20not%20initially%20click%2C%20but%20employees%20stick%20around%20to%20work%20it%20out%20on%20a%20whiteboard%20or%20revisit%20the%20problem%20and%20solve%20it%20later%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20bringing%20employees%20back%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20Jassy%20said%20the%20company%20observed%20an%20improvement%20in%20collaboration%20and%20creative%20problem-solving.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20you%20find%20is%20people%20riff%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other's%20ideas%20better%20if%20they're%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%20%26quot%3BTurns%20out%2C%20sometimes%20it's%20actually%20useful%20to%20interrupt%20each%20other%2C%20because%20you%20get%20to%20a%20faster%20spot%2C%20more%20quickly%2C%20you%20feel%20that%20energy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20when%20employees%20work%20remotely%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20move%20on%20to%20the%20next%20task%20after%20their%20meeting%20ends%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Byou%20just%20don't%20find%20that%20type%20of%20invention%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Amazon%20works%20to%20overhaul%20its%20organizational%20structure%2C%20Jassy%20said%20that%20culture%20isn't%20something%20that%20can%20be%20instilled%20from%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20in%20a%20meeting%20together%2C%20and%20you're%20watching%20the%20body%20language%20and%20you're%20watching%20people's%20expressions%2C%20you%20internalize%20the%20culture%20much%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20added%20that%20teaching%20is%20much%20more%20effective%20if%20you%20can%20walk%20over%20to%20someone%20after%20a%20meeting%20and%20add%20context%20or%20reassurance%20about%20what%20took%20place.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20it%20was%20a%20challenging%20topic%2C%20Jassy%20said%20he%20might%20tell%20a%20colleague%2C%20%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20surprised%20that%20that%20was%20a%20hard%20meeting.%20This%20is%20a%20really%20difficult%20topic.%26quot%3B%20Or%2C%20he%20might%20say%2C%20for%20the%20next%20meeting%2C%20%26quot%3Bthink%20about%20these%20three%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224cbf0a35-1982-4d1d-a3db-26ab41b17f64%5C%22%3ELimiting%20'pre-meetings%20for%20the%20pre-meetings'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-ceo-matt-garman-one-way-door-decision-making-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20has%20a%20concept%20of%20one-way%20and%20two-way%3C%2Fa%3E%20door%20decisions.%20Jassy%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Boverwhelming%20majority%20of%20decisions%26quot%3B%20Amazon%20makes%20are%20two-way%20door%20decisions%2C%20which%20the%20company%20has%20said%20should%20require%20minimal%20executive%20oversight.%20However%2C%20Jassy%20said%20it%20wants%20those%20decisions%20to%20be%20made%20by%20the%20people%20who%20are%20doing%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJassy%20said%20as%20the%20company%20has%20gotten%20larger%2C%20it's%20ended%20up%20with%20increasing%20layers%20of%20management.%20While%20many%20added%20processes%20were%20meant%20to%20bring%20organization%2C%20they've%20led%20to%20a%20place%20where%20there's%20%26quot%3Ba%20pre-meeting%20for%20the%20pre-meeting%20for%20the%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20actually%20making%20those%20decisions%2C%20employees%20may%20also%20feel%20like%20they%20lack%20ownership%20of%20them%2C%20Jassy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20what%20we'd%20like%20to%20try%20and%20limit%2C%26quot%3B%20Jassy%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20really%20want%20our%20owners%20doing%20the%20real%20work%2C%20to%20own%20the%20two-way%20door%20decisions%20and%20to%20be%20able%20to%20move%20quickly%20and%20autonomously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20increase%20the%20ratio%20of%20individual%20contributors%20to%20managers%20by%2015%25%20is%20part%20of%20that%20effort%2C%20Jassy%20said.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-plan-cut-managers-aws-internal-guidelines-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20plan%20also%20includes%20%3C%2Fa%3Edirectives%20for%20managers%20to%20take%20on