ndustry's%20position%20is%20that%20the%20charges%20cover%20legitimate%20services%20tenants%20should%20pay%20for%2C%20and%20some%20landlords%20say%20it's%20long-standing%20practice%20to%20advertise%20rental%20pricing%20without%20fees.%20But%20the%20charges%20have%20also%20been%20labeled%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees.%26quot%3B%20In%202023%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20sought%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-biden-banning-junk-fees-hidden-costs-plane-concert-tickets-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprohibit%20hidden%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20attached%20to%20everything%20from%20concert%20tickets%20to%20hotel%20stays%20to%20rentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20estate%20lobby%20argued%20that%20fees%20are%20not%20deceptive%20and%20that%20landlord-tenant%20relationships%20should%20be%20exempt.%20In%20December%2C%20the%20FTC%20omitted%20rentals%20from%20its%20rule%20in%20favor%20of%20case-by-case%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20FTC%20sued%20the%20property%20management%20firm%20Greystar%2C%20which%20it%20accused%20of%20hiding%20fees%20from%20prospective%20renters.%20(In%20late%20April%2C%20tenants%20in%20California%20filed%20a%20federal%20class%20action%20suit%20alleging%20Greystar%20added%20mandatory%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees%26quot%3B%20while%20advertising%20a%20lower%20rental%20cost.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreystar%20called%20the%20FTC%20suit%20%26quot%3Bagency%20overreach%26quot%3B%20in%20court%20papers%20and%20moved%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%2C%20arguing%20an%20online%20listing%20with%20base%20rent%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20likely%20to%20mislead%26quot%3B%20since%20renters%20understand%20there%20will%20be%20more%20to%20the%20lease%20than%20an%20ad%20says.%20Greystar%20lawyers%20also%20noted%20the%20FTC%20recently%20exempted%20the%20rental%20market%20from%20a%20rule%20on%20deceptive%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Kelly%20Slaughter%2C%20one%20of%20the%20FTC%20commissioners%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%204-1%20vote%20excluding%20rentals%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20bipartisan%20compromise%20and%20not%20a%20suggestion%20that%20renters%20don't%20face%20junk%20fees%20or%20that%20landlords%20aren't%20subject%20to%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20absence%20of%20rental%20fees%20in%20the%20rule%20is%20not%20an%20implicit%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20an%20explicit%2C%20blessing%20of%20the%20practice%20of%20charging%20junk%20fees%20in%20rentals%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%26quot%3BThe%20rule%20we%20passed%20is%20better%20than%20having%20no%20rule%20at%20all.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225138%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FTC%20Commissioner%20Rebecca%20Kelly%20Slaughter%20testifies%20during%20a%20House%20Energy%20and%20Commerce%20subcommittee%20in%20May%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F60edb09b61b8600019f16cc8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223425%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERebecca%20Kelly%20Slaughter%3Cp%3ESusan%20Walsh%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20fired%20Slaughter%20and%20the%20only%20other%20Democratic%20commissioner%20in%20March%2C%20and%20both%20are%20suing%20to%20get%20their%20jobs%20back.%20Slaughter%20and%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bchaos%26quot%3B%20calls%20into%20question%20the%20agency's%20oversight%20of%20rentals%20and%20ongoing%20lawsuits%20against%20landlords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20backlash%20to%20fees%20does%20appear%20to%20be%20having%20some%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2022%20states%20have%20protections%20limiting%20fees%2C%20according%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnlihc.org%2Ftenant-protections%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Low%20Income%20Housing%20Coalition%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Colorado%20passed%20a%20bill%20allowing%20renters%20to%20reuse%20background%20checks%20for%20up%20to%2030%20days%20to%20avoid%20multiple%20fees.%20Massachusetts%20and%20Rhode%20Island%20banned%20application%20fees.%20In%20April%2C%20Illinois'%20House%20of%20Representatives%20passed%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20bar%20landlords%20from%20charging%20a%20move-in%20fee%20and%20limit%20late%20fees%3B%20it's%20pending%20in%20the%20state%20Senate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20an%20industry%20group%20started%20by%20the%20National%20Multifamily%20Housing%20Council%20issued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rettc.org%2Fhubfs%2FMITS%2FDocuments%2FMITS%2520Fee%2520Transparency%2520-%2520Final%2520Proposed%2520Data%2520Model.pdf%3FhsLang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupdated%20data%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20allow%20property%20managers%20to%20standardize%20how%20fees%20are%20displayed%20across%20listing%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20in%20categories%20ranging%20from%20direct%20costs%20such%20as%20%26quot%3Bclean%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bdamage%26quot%3B%20to%20more%20opaque%20buckets%20like%20%26quot%3Badmin%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Baccounting%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bother.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAriel%20Nelson%2C%20a%20staff%20attorney%20with%20the%20National%20Consumer%20Law%20Center%2C%20described%20disclosure%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20most%20minimal%20level%20of%20consumer%20protection%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20such%20efforts%20were%20just%20one%20%26quot%3Bpiece%20of%20this%20puzzle%20to%20make%20it%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e4e8e303-52d9-4732-957b-41099d28fd85%5C%22%3EThe%20age%20of%20luxury%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20court%20records%2C%20interviews%2C%20and%20company%20documents%2C%20Business%20Insider%20traced%20the%20history%20of%20rental%20fees%20%E2%80%94%20from%20early%20experiments%20with%20luxury%20services%20to%20a%20widespread%20practice%20that%20affects%20many%20of%20the%20nation's%2045%20million%20residential%20rental%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20begins%20in%20the%20early%201990s%2C%20when%20overbuilding%20and%20a%20credit%20crunch%20sent%20real%20estate%20into%20a%20downspin.%20The%20federal%20government%20seized%20and%20auctioned%20off%20%24456%20billion%20in%20properties%20and%20other%20assets%20from%20failed%20savings%20and%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20investors%20smelled%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20credit%20markets%20in%20shambles%2C%20this%20new%20crop%20of%20investors%20turned%20to%20the%20public%20market%20to%20fund%20their%20growing%20empires%2C%20using%20a%20newly%20popular%20vehicle%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-is-a-reit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20estate%20investment%20trust%3C%2Fa%3E.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Real%20Estate%20Investment%20Trusts%20trade%20association%2C%20there%20were%20119%20REITs%20in%201990%2C%20with%20a%20total%20market%20value%20of%20%248.7%20billion.%20Nine%20years%20later%2C%20the%20number%20hit%20211%20with%20a%20market%20value%20of%20%24140%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EREITs%20came%20under%20scrutiny%20from%20analysts%20and%20pressure%20from%20investors%20keen%20on%20maximizing%20returns%20at%20a%20challenging%20time%20for%20rental%20housing%2C%20with%20vacancy%20rates%20climbing%20to%20nearly%2011%25%20before%20the%202008%20housing%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20REITs%20looked%20for%20creative%20ways%20to%20attract%20residents%3A%20high-speed%20internet%20and%20home%20theaters%20in%20a%20Dallas%20suburb%2C%20on-site%20day%20care%20in%20Santa%20Monica%2C%20even%20a%20synthy%20music%20album%20titled%20%26quot%3BRenters%20Paradise%26quot%3B%20produced%20by%20Equity%20for%20prospective%20and%20existing%20tenants.%20Equity%20and%20Camden%20Property%20Trust%2C%20which%20bought%20up%20properties%20in%20the%20Sun%20Belt%20and%20went%20public%20in%201993%2C%20used%20amenities%20like%20swimming%20pools%20and%20exercise%20rooms%20to%20stand%20out%20to%20prospective%20luxury%20tenants%20%E2%80%94%20and%20their%20own%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drive%20to%20explore%20non-rental%20revenue%20gained%20steam%20in%202001%20when%20the%20REIT%20Modernization%20Act%20allowed%20these%20landlords%20to%20own%20third-party%20property%20management%20companies.%20Ernst%20%26amp%3B%20Young's%20then%20head%20of%20real%20estate%20said%20the%20change%20would%20allow%20REITs%20to%20%26quot%3Breally%20blow%20these%20activities%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224169%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ric%20Campo%20of%20Camden%20Properties%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681565e83fe8d3928364dc46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222375%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERic%20Campo%20of%20Camden%20Properties%2C%20which%20embraced%20ancillary%20services.%3Cp%3EKaren%20Warren%2FHouston%20Chronicle%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEquity%20Residential's%20Zell%20was%20a%20loud%20voice%20in%20favor%20as%20landlords%20began%20to%20explore%20ancillary%20income%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20every%20dollar%20you%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20Camden's%20CEO%20Ric%20Campo%20said%20in%201996%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20have%20to%20raise%20the%20rent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f91ab03b-bedf-458a-8fa7-473e2719c90e%5C%22%3ESupersizing%20through%20software%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20optimizing%20revenue%20without%20reducing%20costs%20or%20making%20major%20investments%20wasn't%20without%20controversy.%20When%20the%20airline%20industry%20pioneered%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-dynamic-pricing-surge-cost-fatigue-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edynamic%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20tickets%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20found%20it%20tantamount%20to%20illegal%20price%20fixing%20because%20it%20was%20coordinated%20through%20a%20shared%20software%20system.%20(The%20airlines%20settled%20in%201994%2C%20agreeing%20not%20to%20share%20pricing%20information.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20a%20decade%20later%2C%20these%20revenue%20models%20began%20cropping%20up%20in%20rentals.%20Lease%20Rent%20Optimizer%20and%20YieldStar%2C%20which%20suggest%20pricing%20for%20clients'%20units%2C%20were%20among%20the%20early%20tech%20offerings%3B%20several%20were%20bought%20out%20by%20RealPage%2C%20now%20the%20largest%20revenue%20management%20software%20in%20the%20market.%20(RealPage%20is%20the%20target%20of%20a%20DOJ%20suit%20over%20claims%20of%20price%20fixing%20through%20shared%20software%3B%20it%20denied%20that%20its%20software%20has%20anticompetitive%20effects%2C%20called%20the%20lawsuit%20%26quot%3Bbaseless%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20a%20motion%20for%20dismissal%20pending.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20automation%20was%20striking.%20When%20Equity%20tested%20Lease%20Rent%20Optimizer%2C%20an%20executive%20later%20said%2C%20revenue%20increased%20by%203%25%20to%205%25%3B%20in%202006%2C%20Equity%20rolled%20it%20out%20to%20all%20properties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%202008%20housing%20crisis%20hit%2C%20more%20major%20players%20looked%20to%20fees%20to%20replace%20lost%20rents.%20Camden's%202008%20financial%20filings%20show%20revenue%20from%20its%20properties%20jumped%201.5%25%20despite%20low%20occupancy%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECamden's%20then%20president%2C%20Keith%20Oden%2C%20said%20the%20company%20would%20focus%20on%20what%20it%20could%20control%3A%20lowering%20costs%20and%20charging%20fees%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%26quot%3Bnickels-and-dimes%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20called%20it.%20The%20company%20launched%20a%20trash%20service%20similar%20to%20Valet%20Living%2C%20which%20Oden%20predicted%20would%20clear%20%242%20million%20in%20profits%20by%202009.%20(A%20Camden%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20email%20that%20today's%20renters%20had%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20visibility%26quot%3B%20into%20what%20is%20included%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bquoted%20rental%20rate%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20tenants%20appreciated%20its%20%26quot%3Bancillary%20services.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22043f42c5-2be1-4373-a5f1-def69546c9d7%5C%22%3EA%20wave%20of%20corporatization%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fsubprime-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubprime%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20crisis%20also%20accelerated%20investors'%20acquisition%20of%20rental%20housing.%20As%20millions%20of%20borrowers%20lost%20their%20homes%20to%20foreclosure%2C%20investors%20started%20showing%20up%20to%20auctions%20to%20build%20out%20portfolios%20of%20single-family%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%201980%20to%202004%2C%20fewer%20than%20one%20in%20five%20rental%20properties%20were%20bought%20by%20nonindividuals.%20From%202013%20to%202015%2C%20that%20number%20jumped%20to%20nearly%20one%20in%20two.%20And%20with%20more%20corporate%20landlords%20came%20more%20dynamic%20pricing%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20landlords%20expanded%20their%20influence%20over%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20rental%20market%2C%20said%20Jeffrey%20Newsome%2C%20a%20private%20consumer%20protection%20lawyer%20in%20Tampa%2C%20Florida%2C%20who%20represents%20tenants%20in%20several%20class%20action%20lawsuits.%20%26quot%3BThey'd%20like%20to%20make%20money%20out%20of%20every%20single%20aspect%20of%20it%20but%20not%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fbx-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlackstone%3C%2Fa%3E%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20when%20it%20launched%20Invitation%20Homes%20in%202012.%20Within%20five%20years%2C%20the%20company%20owned%2082%2C000%20residential%20properties%2C%20making%20it%20the%20nation's%20largest%20owner%20of%20single-family%20homes%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20firm%20went%20hard%20on%20fees%20as%20it%20went%20public.%20In%202017%2C%20its%20CEO%20said%20%26quot%3Bautomated%20charges%26quot%3B%20helped%20push%20a%2022%25%20increase%20in%20ancillary%20income%20during%20a%20single%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%202019%20investor%20event%2C%20as%20Blackstone%20was%20winding%20down%20its%20investment%2C%20Invitation%20Homes%20announced%20a%20new%20plan%20to%20boost%20revenue%3A%20It%20would%20grow%20its%20auxiliary%20income%20to%20as%20much%20as%20%2430%20million%20by%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20added%20mandatory%20charges%20for%20%26quot%3Butility%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bsmart%20home%20technology%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bair%20filter%20delivery%26quot%3B%20that%20generated%20more%20than%20%2460%20million%20in%20fees%20from%202021%20to%20June%202023%2C%20according%20to%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20FTC%20unfair-practices%20lawsuit%20against%20Invitation%20Homes%2C%20filed%20in%202024%2C%20said%20CEO%20Dallas%20Tanner%20told%20a%20vice%20president%20it%20was%20time%20to%20%26quot%3Bjuice%20this%20hog.%26quot%3B%20The%20suit%20also%20alleged%20that%20in%20a%20November%202021%20slide%20deck%2C%20senior%20leadership%20instructed%20Invitation's%20salesforce%20to%20avoid%20readily%20disclosing%20these%20charges%20to%20prospective%20renters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInvitation%20Homes%20was%20not%20trying%20to%20hide%20any%20fees%2C%20but%20it%20instead%20recognized%20that%20its%20fees%20could%20change%20and%20intended%20to%20ensure%20that%20copy%20was%20always%20as%20accurate%20as%20possible%2C%26quot%3B%20Kristi%20DesJarlais%2C%20a%20company%20spokesperson%2C%20said%20by%20email.%20%26quot%3BNothing%20we%20do%20should%20be%20classified%20as%20a%20'junk%20fee%2C'%20but%20rather%20as%20transparently%20communicated%20services%20that%20directly%20align%20to%20the%20enjoyment%20or%20use%20of%20the%20homes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20settled%20in%20September%20without%20admitting%20wrongdoing%2C%20paying%20%2448%20million%20in%20refunds%20and%20agreeing%20to%20list%20a%20home's%20%26quot%3Btrue%20rental%20price.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Invitation%20Homes%20car%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681537af3fe8d3928364d8c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22554%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20Invitation%20Homes%20car%20in%20Riverside%2C%20California%3Cp%3EMike%20Blake%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20arrived%2C%20along%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feviction-moratorium-ending-what-to-expect-landlords-rents-tenants-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoratorium%20on%20evictions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20corporate%20landlords%20again%20looked%20to%20fees%20to%20plug%20revenue%20holes.%20Camden's%20chief%20financial%20officer%20credited%20utility%20fees%20as%20one%20of%20the%20additions%20that%20helped%20the%20company's%20revenue%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20tenants%20in%20lockdown%2C%20institutional%20apartment%20investors%20buoyed%20by%20cheap%20debt%20went%20on%20another%20buying%20spree.%20RealPage%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20had%20just%20rolled%20out%20new%20updates%20to%20its%20revenue%20management%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ's%20lawsuit%20against%20RealPage%20alleges%20it%20floated%20add-ons%20for%20landlords%2C%20like%20%26quot%3Bweekend%20premiums%26quot%3B%20to%20discourage%20renters%20from%20moving%20on%20weekends%20without%20paying%20a%20fee.%20The%20suit%20added%20several%20landlords%20as%20defendants%20in%20January%2C%20including%20Camden%20and%20Greystar.%20Both%20have%20joined%20other%20landlords%20in%20filing%20motions%20for%20dismissal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224d56fc3a-5e71-4a43-a451-34c68d897701%5C%22%3EThe%20great%20unbundling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlongside%20the%20rise%20of%20service%20fees%20came%20fees%20for%20the%20basics%20of%20life%20as%20a%20renter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECamden%20piloted%20turning%20some%20utilities%20historically%20included%20in%20rent%20into%20a%20revenue%20boost.%20In%20a%201996%20press%20release%20from%20a%20real%20estate%20industry%20group%2C%20the%20Camden%20CEO%20Campo%20said%20the%20company%20cut%20company%20water%20bills%20in%20half%20by%20passing%20costs%20to%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEquity%20Lifestyle%20Properties%2C%20the%20mobile%20home%20and%20RV%20park%20cousin%20of%20Equity%20Residential%2C%20called%20the%20process%20%26quot%3Bunbundling%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20strategy%20to%20charge%20for%20utilities%20separately%20%26quot%3Bevery%20chance%20we%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20CFO%20Paul%20Seavey%20said%20in%20a%202022%20investor%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Equity%20Lifestyle%20spokesperson%2C%20Jennifer%20Ludovice%2C%20said%20by%20email%20that%20the%20company%20used%20unbundling%20%26quot%3Bto%20increase%20transparency%20in%20billing%20and%20allow%20residents%20better%20control%20of%20their%20expenses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20rebilling%20services%20help%20landlords%20remove%20those%20costs%20from%20their%20books.%20They%20act%20as%20an%20intermediary%20between%20tenants%20and%20utilities%20and%20typically%20charge%20tenants%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20utilities%20plus%20an%20administrative%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20group%20of%20tenants%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20tried%20to%20find%20out%20how%20much%20extra%20they%20were%20paying.%20They%20compared%20utility%20costs%20for%20two%20one-bedroom%20apartments%3A%20a%20913-square-foot%20unit%20in%20their%20building%2C%20Guild%20Lofts%2C%20owned%20by%20the%20asset%20manager%20Brookfield%2C%20and%20a%20728-square-foot%20apartment%20in%20the%20older%20Insignia%20on%20M%2C%20owned%20by%20the%20real%20estate%20firm%20Bozzuto.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20consumption%2C%20the%20Brookfield%20tenant%20paid%20nearly%20%2440%20in%20utility%20fees%20in%20June%20%E2%80%94%20almost%20half%20of%20them%20to%20a%20Brookfield-owned%20water%20metering%20service.%20The%20Bozzuto%20tenant%20paid%20%2419%20in%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrookfield%20told%20Guild%20Lofts%20tenants%20in%20their%202024%20lease%20amendments%20that%20they%20would%20be%20hit%20with%20a%20new%20%26quot%3Bcommon%20area%20electricity%26quot%3B%20charge%2C%20which%20included%20charges%20for%20heating%20and%20cooling%20tenants'%20own%20units%20and%20common%20areas%20like%20the%20lobby.%20This%20charge%2C%20which%20changes%20month%20to%20month%20based%20on%20building%20use%20and%20for%20which%20tenants%20don't%20see%20the%20underlying%20calculation%2C%20added%20about%20%24100%20a%20month%20to%20the%20tenants'%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarket%20giants%20like%20Brookfield%20view%20our%20homes%20as%20assets%2C%20and%20their%20only%20objective%20is%20to%20squeeze%20residents%20for%20profits%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20No%C3%ABlle%20Porter%2C%20an%20organizer%20for%20Brookfield%20DC%20Tenants%20and%20director%20of%20government%20affairs%20for%20the%20National%20Housing%20Law%20Project.%20%26quot%3BDeceptive%20and%20even%20illegal%20fees%20are%20on%20the%20rise%20across%20the%20country%2C%20and%20overburdened%20renters%20cannot%20afford%20%24200%2C%20%24300%2C%20%24400%20per%20month%20in%20additional%2C%20surprise%20charges%20and%20fees.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20tenant's%20December%20class%20action%20suit%20accused%20Brookfield%20of%20violating%20local%20laws%20with%20hidden%20utility%20charges.%20Brookfield%20said%20in%20a%20filing%20that%20the%20case%20should%20be%20dismissed%20because%20it%20%26quot%3Bexpressly%20told%20its%20tenants%2C%20including%20Plaintiff%2C%20exactly%20what%20they%20were%20paying%20for%20and%20exactly%20what%20they%20were%20receiving%20in%20return.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20an%20April%20email%20exchange%20between%20Brookfield%20and%20its%20utility%20billing%20partner%2C%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20showed%20they%20were%20accidentally%20overbilling%20some%20units%20at%20a%20Navy%20Yard%20property%20called%20Foundry%20Loft%20for%20gas%2C%20stormwater%2C%20and%20trash.%20A%20Brookfield%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20company%20is%20now%20conducting%20%26quot%3Ba%20complete%20review%20of%20billing%26quot%3B%20across%20the%20Navy%20Yard%20properties%2C%20and%20the%20company%20is%20distributing%20about%20%244%20a%20month%20to%20Foundry%20Loft%20tenants%20for%20gas%2C%20stormwater%2C%20and%20trash%20overbilling%20from%20June%202023%20to%20April%202025%2C%20according%20to%20an%20email%20obtained%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20care%20a%20great%20deal%20about%20being%20fair%20and%20transparent%20in%20pricing%20apartment%20homes%20to%20be%20consistent%20with%20market%20demand%20and%20in%20line%20with%20all%20regulatory%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20to%20BI%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20other%20tenants%20are%20now%20being%20charged%20for%20the%20simple%20act%20of%20paying%20the%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELandlords%20who%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fstocks%2Fappf-stock%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAppFolio%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20property%20management%20tech%20company%20whose%20software%20is%20used%20to%20manage%20over%208%20million%20properties%2C%20may%20pass%20onto%20tenants%20those%20fees%3A%20%242.49%20for%20each%20eCheck%20or%203.49%25%20of%20their%20rent%20if%20they%20use%20a%20credit%20card%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20be%20%2470%20a%20month%20on%20a%20median%20US%20rent%20of%20%242%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221758%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20tenant%20letter%20to%20the%20FTC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68151f04a466d2b74ab4eb71%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22428%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20FTC%20proposed%20a%20rule%20on%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees%26quot%3B%20that%20received%20public%20comments.%20The%20final%20rule%20exempted%20landlords.%20Asked%20about%20this%20comment%20about%20fees%20to%20pay%20the%20rent%2C%20PhillyLiving%20Management%20Group%20said%20they%20do%20not%20profit%20from%20the%20fees.%3Cp%3EFTC%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%20has%20been%20lucrative.%20In%20January%202024%2C%20the%20company's%20CFO%20at%20the%20time%2C%20Fay%20Sien%20Goon%2C%20said%20%26quot%3Bvalue%20added%20services%26quot%3B%20had%20contributed%20to%20year-over-year%20revenue%20growth%20of%2039%25%2C%20partially%20driven%20by%2048%25%20growth%20in%20ancillary%20revenue.%20%26quot%3BCard%20adoption%20for%20rent%20payments%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bcontinued%20to%20exceed%20our%20expectations.%26quot%3B%20AppFolio%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20multiple%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e8e64fb0-21e3-4e8e-bc88-056c50147a00%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'The%20market%20has%20determined%20that%20it's%20fair'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20housing-related%20fees%20are%20imposed%20by%20landlords.%20Third-party%20vendors%20are%20now%20competing%20for%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20action%2C%20promising%20to%20trim%20costs%20and%20drive%20revenue%20for%20landlords%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-and-pop-landlords-homeownership-rent-wall-street-corporate-investors-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emom-and-pop%20property%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20by%20providing%20fee-based%20services%20like%20garbage%20collection%20or%20offering%20%26quot%3Bresident%20benefits%26quot%3B%20like%20air%20filter%20delivery%20and%20move-in%20%26quot%3Bconcierge%26quot%3B%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EValet%20Living%2C%20owned%20by%20private%20equity%2C%20has%20become%20the%20nation's%20largest%20provider%20of%20doorstep%20trash%20collection.%20One%20of%20its%20sales%20presentations%20said%20the%20service%20could%20add%20an%20average%20of%20%2440%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20net%20operating%20income%20for%20a%20landlord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20Valet%20Living%20said%20that%20it%20didn't%20set%20prices%20or%20collect%20money%20directly%20and%20that%20the%20company%20supported%20%26quot%3Btransparent%20fee%20structures%20that%20allow%20residents%20to%20understand%20all%20housing%20amenities%20and%20costs%20before%20they%20move-in%20or%20sign%20a%20renewal.%26quot%3B%20A%20spokesperson%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20question%20about%20how%20the%20firm%20would%20increase%20net%20operating%20income%20for%20landlords%2C%20or%20whether%20it%20charges%20landlords%20directly%20and%20then%20encourages%20landlords%20to%20mark%20up%20the%20service%20to%20make%20a%20profit%20off%20of%20their%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhottest-proptech-startups-2024-according-to-venture-capitalists-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproptech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20property%20technology%2C%20fueled%20by%20a%20venture%20capital%20spend%20that%20peaked%20at%20%2432%20billion%20in%202021%2C%20has%20further%20spurred%20the%20rise%20of%20third-party%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELatchel%2C%20which%20launched%20in%202017%2C%20offers%20landlords%20a%20%26quot%3Bresident%20benefit%20package%26quot%3B%20that%20includes%20pest%20relief%2C%20a%20drain%20snake%2C%20and%20reimbursements%20for%20accidental%20damage%20to%20a%20unit%2C%20for%20a%20fee%20of%202%25%20to%203%25%20of%20the%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20%2440%20to%20%2460%20a%20month%20on%20the%20national%20median%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20then%20be%20passed%20on%20to%20the%20tenant.%20Latchel%2C%20which%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20BI%2C%20advertises%20that%20by%20outsourcing%20a%20landlord's%20maintenance%20costs%2C%20Latchel%20can%20generate%20savings%20of%20up%20to%20%2420%20a%20unit%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20vendors%2C%20such%20as%20CredHub%2C%20charge%20landlords%20to%20report%20rent%20payments%20to%20credit%20agencies.%20Chris%20Dukelow%2C%20CredHub's%20cofounder%2C%20said%20that%20unlike%20add-ons%20%26quot%3Bused%20more%20to%20make%20money%26quot%3B%20from%20tenants%2C%20rent%20reporting%20was%20beneficial.%20He%20said%20that%20tenants%20should%20be%20allowed%20to%20opt%20out%20or%20have%20the%20cost%20folded%20into%20their%20rent%20but%20that%20most%20CredHub%20clients%20marked%20up%20the%20cost%20through%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20it's%20up%20to%20the%20property%20manager%20what%20they%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Ortscheid%20is%20a%20partner%20in%20PMAssist%2C%20a%20consulting%20company%20that%20helps%20property%20managers%20pursue%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bfee-maxing%26quot%3B%20through%20online%20courses%20that%20lay%20out%20more%20than%2075%20kinds%20of%20fees%20that%20can%20be%20charged.%20Ortscheid%20declined%20to%20comment%20but%20publicly%20credits%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20his%20own%20property%20management%20company's%20revenue%20to%20fees%20charged%20to%20tenants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrtscheid%20provides%20services%20mostly%20to%20single-family%20homes%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-orders-accidental-landlords-sell-rent-home-mortgage-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccidental%20landlords%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20inherit%20a%20rental%20property%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%94%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%20from%20massive%20REITs.%20He%20credits%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Residential%20Property%20Managers%20conference%20with%20introducing%20him%20to%20%26quot%3Bfee-maxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRemember%2C%20if%20a%20tenant%20will%20pay%20it%2C%20the%20market%20has%20determined%20that%20it's%20fair%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20webinar%20recording%20viewed%20by%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2272532bfa-f41e-4965-a421-c17ec82461c7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Pushing%20the%20envelope'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%20have%20been%20slow%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20the%20spread%20of%20rental%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20a%20California%20judge%20ruled%20that%20Equity%20crossed%20the%20line%20with%20a%205%25%20late-payment%20fee%20that%20violated%20a%20state%20ban%20on%20marking%20up%20fees%3B%20the%20judge%20found%20that%20the%20company%20had%20charged%20more%20than%20%2436%20million%20in%20late%20fees%20in%20California%20over%20nearly%2011%20years%20and%20agreed%20with%20the%20general%20structure%20of%20the%20plaintiffs'%20calculations%20that%20found%20%2426%20million%20of%20that%20was%20excessive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20response%20to%20the%20filing%2C%20Equity%20argued%20that%20the%20calculations%20didn't%20take%20into%20account%20rising%20personnel%20costs%20and%20argued%20that%20the%20court%20should%20limit%20monetary%20relief.%20On%20an%20April%202024%20earnings%20call%2C%20CEO%20Mark%20Parrell%20said%20the%20company%20was%20considering%20an%20appeal.%20McKenna%2C%20the%20Equity%20Residential%20spokesperson%2C%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20evidence%20in%20the%20case%20included%20a%202008%20internal%20document%20on%20%26quot%3Bthe%20potential%20upside%26quot%3B%20of%20hiking%20late%20fees%20to%205%25%20of%20rent.%20Denise%20Beihoffer%2C%20the%20company's%20vice%20president%20for%20legal%20affairs%2C%20said%20Equity%20was%20%26quot%3Bcommitted%20to%20pushing%20the%20envelope%20a%20bit%20where%20the%20risk%20of%20doing%20so%20is%20low.%26quot%3B%20The%20firm's%20vice%20president%20of%20financial%20planning%20at%20the%20time%20told%20her%20in%20a%20May%202008%20email%20that%20it%20looked%20like%20a%20%26quot%3Bslam%20dunk%26quot%3B%3B%20because%20California's%20average%20rent%20was%20%241%2C500%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20average%20late%20fee%20would%20come%20in%20at%20%2475%2C%26quot%3B%20a%2050%25%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20have%20been%20a%20reasonable%20calculation%3A%20The%20FTC%20has%20gone%20after%20only%20a%20few%20landlords%20over%20rental%20fees%20recently.%20And%20the%20impact%20of%20voluntary%20transparency%20efforts%20has%20been%20uneven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Biden%20White%20House's%20push%20to%20ban%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20listing%20portals%20Zillow%2C%20Apartments.com%2C%20and%20AffordableHousing.com%20agreed%20to%20display%20fees%20and%20calculate%20the%20total%20cost%20of%20renting%20for%20renters.%20But%20that%20can%20be%20only%20so%20effective.%20A%20Zillow%20spokesperson%2C%20Emily%20McDonald%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20fees%20showed%20up%20only%20%26quot%3Bwhen%20landlords%20and%20property%20managers%20provide%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226567%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Joe%20Biden%20at%20an%20event%20on%20%26quot%3Bjunk%20fees.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68156ac3a466d2b74ab4f541%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224378%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20called%20for%20restrictions%20on%20so-called%20junk%20fees%2C%20but%20ultimately%20did%20not%20include%20rentals%20in%20the%20new%20rule.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSusan%20Walsh%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EListings%20within%20a%20property%20manager's%20control%20may%20not%20be%20complete.%20In%20the%20FTC%20case%20against%20Greystar%2C%20the%20agency%20said%20the%20company%20was%20not%20listing%20all%20fees%20on%20its%20sites.%20The%20lack%20of%20transparency%20had%20cost%20renters%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%20the%20suit%20says%2C%20citing%20one%20tenant%20whose%20actual%20monthly%20cost%20was%2040%25%20higher%20than%20what%20they%20were%20quoted%20when%20signing%20the%20lease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%2C%20Greystar%20said%20no%20tenants%20paid%20any%20fee%20%26quot%3Bthey%20have%20not%20seen%20and%20agreed%20to%20in%20their%20lease%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20it%20had%20expressed%20willingness%2C%20in%20discussions%20with%20the%20FTC%2C%20to%20%26quot%3Bdisplay%20total%20monthly%20leasing%20price%26quot%3B%20whenever%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bwithin%20Greystar's%20control.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGreystar%20also%20said%20the%20FTC%20provided%20%26quot%3Bzero%20guidance%26quot%3B%20when%20it%20decided%20to%20exempt%20landlords%20from%20its%20rule%20on%20fee%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20effective%20path%20to%20achieving%20uniform%20and%20consistent%20fee%20disclosures%20is%20through%20clear%20regulatory%20guidelines%20for%20our%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20disappointing%20that%20the%20FTC%20has%20failed%20to%20show%20any%20leadership%20in%20this%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20via%20email%20at%20anicoll%40businessinsider.com%20and%20creyes%40businessinsider.com.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsecure-news-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjunk-fees-rental-apartment-housing-costs-history-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746259381000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68152538c6ad288d147fe946%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjunk-fees-rental-apartment-housing-costs-history-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22What%20started%20out%20as%20fees%20for%20luxury%20amenities%20morphed%20into%20a%20juggernaut%20to%20charge%20tenants%20extra%20%E2%80%94%20even%20for%20the%20act%20of%20paying%20rent.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22anicoll%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Nicoll%2CCecilia%20Reyes)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A